Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: guillotina_amqp
Version: 1.0.7
Summary: Integrate amqp into guillotina
Home-page: https://github.com/guillotinaweb/guillotina_amqp
Author: Nathan Van Gheem
Author-email: vangheem@gmail.com
License: BSD
Description: guillotina_amqp Docs
        --------------------
        
        Integrates aioamqp into guillotina.
        
        
        Configuration
        -------------
        
        Example docs::
        
        
            {
                "amqp": {
        	       "host": "localhost",
        	       "port": 5673,
                   "login": "guest",
                   "password": "guest",
                   "vhost": "/",
                   "heartbeat": 800
        	    }
            }
        
        
        Dependencies
        ------------
        
        Python >= 3.6
        
        
        Installation
        ------------
        
        This example will use virtualenv::
        
        
            virtualenv .
            ./bin/pip install .[test]
        
        
        Running
        -------
        
        Most simple way to get running::
        
            ./bin/guillotina
        
        
        Queue tasks
        -----------
        
        code::
        
            from guillotina_amqp import add_task
            await add_task(my_func, 'foobar', kw_arg='blah')
        
        
        With decorators
        ---------------
        
        code::
        
            from guillotina_amqp import task
        
            @task
            async def my_func(foo):
                print(foo)
        
            await my_func('bar')
        
        
        Run the worker
        --------------
        
        command::
        
            g amqp-worker
        
